Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre

Interface Solution<A extends Action>

Type Parameters:
A - the type of action this solution is made of
All Superinterfaces:
Countable, Iterable<A>, Plan<A>, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
SolutionGoal, SolutionPlan
public interface Solution<A extends Action> extends Serializable, Plan<A>
A solution is a plan for an character to achieve a goal that also includes explanations for every action in the plan. Solutions are not checked for validity, so partial or incorrect solutions can be constructed without causing an exception.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • getExplanation

      Solution<A> getExplanation(Character character)
      Returns a solution explaining how the first action in this solution would contribute to increasing the given character's utility. If the given character is this solution's character, this method returns this solution. If the given character is not a consenting character to the first action or if no solution has been set for the given character, this method returns null. If an explanation is returned, its first action will be the same as the first action in this solution.
      Parameters:
      character - the character for whom an explanation of this solution's first action is desired
      Returns:
      an explanation for how the character believes the first action in this solution will contribute to increasing their utility, or null if the character is not a consenting character to the action or no explanation has been set

    • prepend

      Solution<A> prepend(A action)
      Adds an action to the beginning of this solution. Validity is not checked, meaning there are no guarantees that this action actually contributes to the solution or is non-redundant. Initially, the action will have no explanations; those can be set.
      Parameters:
      action - the action to added to the beginning of the solution
      Returns:
      a new solution with the given action at the beginning

    • setExplanation

      Solution<A> setExplanation(Solution<A> explanation)
      Sets an explanation for the first action of this solution. The explanation will be set for the given solution's character. If a different solution is already set for that character, it will be replaced. The explanation must not be for this solution's character, and it must begin with the same first action that this solution begins with.
      Parameters:
      explanation - an explanation for the first action
      Returns:
      a new solution with this explanation set for its character
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if this solution has no actions
      IllegalArgumentException - if the given explanation does not begin with the same action as this solution
      IllegalArgumentException - if the given explanation is for the this solution's character or if the given solution is for a character who is not a consenting character of this solution's first action
